<HEADLINE>
N.Y. TIMES REPORTERS CITED FOR EXCELLENCE IN SPORTS COVERAGE 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Selena Roberts of The New York Times won first place
in The Associated Press Sports Editors national contest for her May
16, 1999, account of the New York Knicks' decisive Game 5 victory
over the Miami Heat during last season's National Basketball
Association Eastern Conference playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   Jere Longman, Kirk Johnson and Jo Thomas of The Times were
awarded second place in results announced Tuesday for their
three-month investigation into the scandal surrounding the
International Olympic Committee and the Salt Lake City Olympic bid.
First place in the category went to The St. Paul Pioneer Press for
its investigation into the University of Minnesota men's basketball
program. &QL;
</P>
