<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   NASA-FAILURES (San Francisco) _ Embarrassed by two recent launch
failures, NASA might have to conserve its resources by developing a
less diverse array of space missions to Mars, a high-ranking space
agency scientist says. By KEAY DAVIDSON.
</P>
<P>
   MINORITIES-ENVIRONMENT (Essex, N.Y.) _ The Adirondack Park, the
East Coast's largest parcel of wilderness, attracts hundreds of
thousands of visitors a year. But to an increasing number of
people, it is a mystery why the mountains of northern New York
state attract few minorities. The situation is not unique to the
Adirondacks _ environmentalists around the country are increasingly
concerned about the lack of minority involvement in wilderness
issues. By ALAN WECHSLER.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   INVESTMENT-ADVICE (San Francisco) _ The advice from financial
advisors in the midst of this bout of market volatility is like a
mantra: Stick with your long-term, diversified investment plan, and
don't do anything rash. By VICTORIA COLLIVER.
</P>
<P>
   CAREER-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ Which is more important: making
a hard job look easy or an easy job look hard? The answer, of
course, is ``yes.'' Society loves people who make a hard job look
easy, with the grace of a Magic Johnson or the dexterity of a
classic chef or the poise of an Oprah Winfrey. Nowhere on a
bestseller list will you find ``How to be a Millionaire by
Scrimping and Saving and Busting Your Hump for 40 Years.'' By DAVE
MURPHY.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-REVIEW-BLACKANDWHITE (Undated) _ The tag line for ``Black
and White,'' James Toback's improvisatory investigation of hip-hop
culture and the white kids who've embraced it, asks: ``What happens
when you mix it up?'' You should answer, ``Ideological disaster!''
Then wave your hands in the air, wave 'em like you just don't care.
It's that kind of experiment. By WESLEY MORRIS.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-MASTERS (Augusta, Ga.) _ It's not often that a member of
Augusta National holds a press conference in his green jacket, but
let's cut Arnold Palmer some slack _ he's new at this. Not new at
the green jacket (he's won four) and not new at press conferences
(he's had umpteen zillion), just new to paying dues. By SUSAN
FORNOFF.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ The heck with ``the old economy''
and ``the new economy.'' I want a piece of the Willie economy. Our
mayor jumped with both well-shod feet into the stock market last
year and made a killing, largely on initial public offerings of
high-tech stocks, doubling his investment to almost a million
bucks. According to his spokeswoman, Kandace Bender, he doesn't
have a new financial advisor but is ``kind of playing around on the
Internet and doing trading over the Internet.'' By ROB MORSE.
</P>
</TEXT>
