   SCI-OZONE-DEPLETE (Undated) _ Researchers from NASA and other
agencies said Wednesday that they have recorded one of the worst
losses of stratospheric ozone in the Arctic, coming near the end of
one of the coldest winters on record in the polar stratosphere. The
finding heightens concern that changes in the global climate may
delay recovery of the earth's partly depleted ozone layer. By
William K. Stevens.
