   DRUG-PRICES (Washington) _ The political potency of the high
price of prescription drugs was powerfully demonstrated on two
fronts Wednesday. A mainstream Republican senator complained about
the disparity between prescription drugs in Canada and the United
States. And although Democrats have been making this point for
months, the drug lobby is in a panic now that Republicans are
adding a voice to the criticism. And in the Senate, Democrats have
forced a symbolic vote on the issue as an amendment to a budget
resolution. By Robert Pear.
