<P>
   GLF-MASTERS (Augusta, Ga.) _ Hal Sutton caught himself. Augusta
National, where the Masters begins tomorrow, is a shrine; playing
in the tournament is a privilege. Criticism will get him nowhere,
so he shifts focus. By Jim McCabe. 1050 words.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-COL-NOTEBOOK (Indianapolis) _ In the litany of championship
moments, Michigan State's 89-76 win over Florida in the NCAA title
game should be put near the top. By Mark Blaudschun. 775 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   BKC-RYAN-COLUMN (Indianapolis) _ It's a very good thing for
Michigan State that the young Mateen Cleaves was not your basic
frontrunner. By Bob Ryan. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   SKI-KOZNICK (Undated) _ After two back-to-back slalom wins to
put a blazing finale on her World Cup season for the U.S. Ski Team,
Kristina Koznick had all but forgotten what a short leap it had
been from the lowest point in her career to the heights. By Tony
Chamberlain. 1340 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-SHAUGHNESSY-COLUMN (Seattle) _ For Pedro Martinez, it was
business as usual against the Mariners. By Dan Shaughnessy. PHOTO
</P>
