<P>
   PIERO-FRESCOS (Arezzo, Italy) _ After 15 years of arduous,
costly high-tech restoration, the scaffolding has come down in the
Basilica of San Francesco, giving an adoring public a dramatic new
look at one of the art world's splendors, the fresco cycle ``Legend
of the True Cross'' by the 15th-century Renaissance painter and
mathematician Piero della Francesca. By Ralph Blumenthal.
</P>
<P>
   AIDA-HEADLEY (New York) _ A major moment for Broadway newcomer
Heather Headley in ``Aida.'' By Robin Pogrebin.
</P>
<P>
   POMPEII-EROTICA (Naples, Italy) _ The contents of the ``Secret
Cabinet'' that were so scandalous they were kept locked up for most
of the last 200 years will be unveiled to the public next week.
Curators delicately refer to the ``Secret Cabinet'' or the
``Forbidden Collection,'' but museum guards loudly direct visitors
to ``Il Pornografico.'' By Alessandra Stanley.
</P>
<P>
   LANCASTER-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Burt Lancaster: An American
Life,'' by Kate Buford (Knopf). Reviewed by Mel Gussow.
</P>
