r d BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP06-COX     04-05 0451
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP06-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Quick and easy candy simply divine
 &HT;    By Marcia Langhenry
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ You know that kitchen drawer crammed with booklets and
warranties from electric carving knives, coffeemakers and
refrigerators collected since the day you set up housekeeping? If
you're like me, you believe that the day you throw them out will be
the very day you might need them.
</P>
<P>
   Janet Cornelson of Gainesville, Ga., proves the value of hanging
on, mess notwithstanding. She turned to the circa-1981 recipe
booklet that came with her microwave oven and happily was able to
fulfill Gayle Ledbetter's request for the microwave divinity she
and her sister used to make.
</P>
<P>
   Unlike most, this divinity is virtually foolproof and comes out
well no matter what the weather. And it tastes the same and takes
much less time, Cornelson said.
</P>
<P>
   It does contain raw egg whites, though, so you might not want to
serve it to very young children, the elderly or those with weakened
immune systems.
</P>
<P>
   CANDY
</P>
<P>
   Microwave
</P>
<P>
   Divinity
</P>
<P>
   Makes 30 pieces
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: 30 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Cooking time: 12 to 17 minutes
</P>
<P>
   2 cups granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup cold water
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1 egg white
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon vanilla
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup chopped nuts
</P>
<P>
   Combine sugar, water and vinegar in a buttered 4-cup glass
measure; cover with plastic wrap. Microwave 12 to 17 minutes on
medium-high (roast) or until candy forms a firm ball in cold water
(240 degrees). Meanwhile, beat egg white in medium mixer bowl until
stiff peaks form. Pour candy syrup in thin stream into egg white,
beating constantly with mixer. Add vanilla; beat until mixture is
stiff. Fold in nuts. Drop mixture by teaspoonsful onto wax paper;
cool.
</P>
<P>
   Per piece: 65 calories, no protein, 1 gram fat (percent calories
from fat, 17), 14 grams carbohydrates, no cholesterol, 2 milligrams
sodium, no fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Request
</P>
<P>
   Jean Manker of Roswell, Ga., is looking for a Caramel Chess
Cake.
</P>
<P>
   Update
</P>
<P>
   Recently we reported that Don Pepino pizza sauce is available
for purchase online by the case. Sharon Fleitman e-mailed us to say
it is also available locally at Ingles markets and Quality Kosher
Emporium.
</P>
<P>
   Contacting this column
</P>
<P>
   Recipes or requests to be published in this column should be
sent to Recipe Swap, Food Department, The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. Fax:
404-526-5509. Include a daytime phone number. E-mail:
mlanghenry(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   Published recipes
</P>
<P>
   For a copy of a recipe previously published in the newspaper,
call the Stacks at 404-526-5668.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
