appearance some see as awkward in light of the federal antitrust
suit. (Glass, Cox News Service). 8.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ Both sides in the Microsoft antitrust
case meet with U.S. District Judge Thomas Penfield Jackson on
Wednesday, after which a schedule for the trial's next phase will
be issued. Jackson has said he hopes that any appeal can be
expedited directly to the Supreme Court, meaning the case might be
completed within a year. (Glass, Cox News Service). 15.
