   These sports stories for release Thursday, April 6, 2000, are
moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BKC-GATECH-HEWITT _ ATLANTA _ Georgia Tech has ended its search
for a men's basketball coach with the hiring of Siena coach Paul
Hewitt. Hewitt becomes the first black basketball coach in Georgia
Tech history and only the third in ACC history. Why did it take so
long for Tech athletics director Dave Braine to hire a replacement
for Bobby Cremins, who resigned Feb. 18? (Clemons, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BKC-HEWITT-PROFILE _ ATLANTA _ It's a question that Georgia Tech
fans are bound to ask - who is Paul Hewitt? Hewitt is not familiar
name to most ACC basketball fans, having spent most of his coaching
career in the Northeast. But he's well-respected among basketball
coaches and has been presented with the task of turning around the
Georgia Tech program. A look at the background of Hewitt including
previous coaching stops, past successess, etc. (Clemons, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-ROCKIES _ ATLANTA _ Coverage of the Atlanta Braves
vs. Colorado Rockies. (CRogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: First pitch is at 7:40 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR
</P>
<P>
   CAR-LEEPETTY-OBIT _ Lee Petty, winner of the first Daytona 500
and patriarch of one of racing's royal families, died Wednesday at
86. He was one of the princes of racing during the stock-car
circuit's infancy in the 1940s and 1950s. Petty, who died at Moses
Cone Hospital in Greensboro several weeks after undergoing surgery
for a stomach aneurysm, was the father of Winston Cup great Richard
Petty, grandfather of Kyle Petty and great-grandfather of Adam
Petty, who made his Winston Cup debut last weekend in Texas.
(Minter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF/MASTERS
</P>
<P>
   GLF-MASTERS-ADVANCE _ AUGUSTA, Ga. _ Advancing the Masters,
which begins Thursday. (Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   GLF-MASTERS-TEE _ AUGUTSA, Ga. _ Many golfers say the first shot
at a Ryder Cup is the most pressurized shot in golf. Try telling
that to those who will stand on the No. 1 teebox at Augusta this
morning. The pressure is about the same. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-MASTERS-CRENSHAW _ AUGUSTA, Ga. _ Whatever happened to Ben
Crenshaw and his golf game? Crenshaw, a past Masters champion,
might be best remembered for leading the Ryder Cup team to victory
in 1999 than his play in the PGA. (Bohks, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/NFL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DRAFT-FRANKS _ Miami tight end Bubba Franks could have been
a major-college basketball prospect, but his high school coach hid
the recruiting letters from him. It's a good thing _ Franks is
projected as the top tight end available in the draft (Schlabach,
Atanta Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-CANOE-TRIALS _ Advance canoe/kayak Olympic trials on the
Ocoee River. (Mitchell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER
</P>
<P>
