<HEADER>
A8049 &Cx1f; taf-z
u l BC-MINI-DISHWASHERS-NYT &LR;      04-05 0294
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MINI-DISHWASHERS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MICRO-APPLIANCES EASE LIFE IN MACRO-CLOSETS 
</HEADLINE>
  (ART ADV: Photo is being sent to NYT photo clients. Nonsubscribers
can purchase one-time rights by calling 888-603-1036 or
888-346-9867.) 
 By   KATHLEEN   McELROY   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The Equator Mini-Maid dishwasher is small enough to
sit on a countertop. Though it is bigger than a breadbox (if square
in shape), it is as portable as a microwave or a 13-inch
television. The modest size might make it the renter's solution to
dishpan hands.
</P>
<P>
   The dishwasher, about 19} inches on each side, can also be
mounted in a cabinet as a miniature version of the high-end
dishwasher drawer. The Mini-Maid's two models are not for scrubbing
big pots or cookie sheets.
</P>
<P>
   The PLS 602 S (about $370) has four wash-cycle settings and may
hold as many as eight full place settings.
</P>
<P>
   The PLS 600 (just introduced at $300), is a party giver's dream:
it is designed for glassware, especially martini glasses.
</P>
<P>
   The same company also offers space-saving appliances for
clothes. The EZ 3,600 CEE (about $900) is one of its ``clothes
processors,'' which combine a washer and a dryer in one unit, a
combination long popular in Europe. Because the combination clothes
washers and dryers are ventless, they can be installed under a
kitchen counter.
</P>
<P>
   This one can do a few shirts, two or three pairs of jeans,
perhaps the contents of one pillow case. The total time for washing
and drying can be two hours, but it is faster than hand washing and
air drying, without the need to drape laundry on a shower rod.
</P>
<P>
   Both appliances can be hard to find in stores. Information is
available from Equator at (800) 935-1955 or from the company's Web
site, www.equatorappl.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
