   STOCKS-MARKETPLACE (New York) _ The new economy stocks may be
battered, but they are not dead. Even if the high-technology
companies led the market down in the rout that ended about 1:15
p.m. on Tuesday, those same stocks generally recovered the most
during the next day and a half. By Floyd Norris.
