   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   NY-LAPD-RECRUIT (New York) _ Faced with calls to increase the
diversity of its force and an expected exodus of officers, the New
York City Police Department embarked on an ambitious recruiting
drive over the past several years. But the department has learned
that the drive produced only 5,500 people interested in taking the
qualifying test this year, a 50 percent drop from the year before.
As New York struggles to lure its residents to its own department,
police recruiters from Los Angeles have come to the New York Police
Department's own hiring turf with promises of warmer climes, higher
starting salaries and openings at the academy as soon as this
summer. By C.J. Chivers. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a''
news file.)
