<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Gore in Florida for fund-raiser
 &HT;    By Brian E. Crowley
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Vice President Al Gore will be at the home of
attorney Bob Montgomery tonight for a $10,000-per-person dinner.
</P>
<P>
   On Friday, Gore travels to Old School Square in Delray Beach,
where he will meet with voters and talk about Medicare and his plan
to make it easier to get prescription drugs.
</P>
<P>
   At the meeting, with an invited crowd of about 150, Gore also is
expected to talk about the Democratic Party platform and a plan to
allow people to send suggestions about changing the party platform
over the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   The Democratic National Committee has formed a partnership with
Speakout.Com, a Web site that helps people find out about issues
and contact their elected officials. Gore and the DNC plan to use
Speakout.Com to allow people to read the party platform and make
comments.
</P>
<P>
   After the morning meeting at Old School Square, Gore will travel
to the Broward County home of U.S. Rep. Peter Deutsch, where he
will attend a $5,000-a-person lunch with about 85 people.
</P>
<P>
   The more than $1 million expected to be raised from the dinner
and lunch is going to the Democratic National Committee. That money
will be used to help elect Democratic candidates, including Gore,
who is challenging Texas Gov. George W. Bush for the presidency.
</P>
<P>
   After lunch, Gore is scheduled to travel to Tampa, where he will
go to an after-school program, meet with children and teachers and
talk about education.
</P>
<P>
   Gore is tentatively scheduled to return to West Palm Beach on
Monday to raise more money for the Democratic Party. For in-depth
reporting, opinion and cartoonists, visit the Cox News Campaign
2000 Web site: http://www.coxnews.com/2000.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
