   There are not many milkmen these days making the rounds of
America's towns and suburbs. But Westchester County has at least
one, Hercules Bontzolakes, 48, who is the old-fashioned, ``pay when
you can, cream floats to the top,'' real McCoy, the classic
purveyor of milk, cream, cottage cheese, eggs and juice.
Bontzolakes, checks orders in his truck while on his route. (Joyce
Dopkeen/The New York Times) LITE
</P>
