AFRICA-DIAMONDS-4-B&AMP;W -- The value of diamonds, coupled with the
anonymity and portability of the stones, have made them one of the
most potent, and dangerous, currencies of modern Africa. Near
Kisangani, miners use picks and shovels to dig to the gravel layer
in which diamonds can be found in this 1997 photo. (Stephen
