<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving Wednesay, 04/05/00. Photo
clients will automatically receive these photos via AP's
PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling
(888) 603-1036 or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT49) NEW YORK -- April 5, 2000 -- NY-FASHION-HELP --
Originally a concession to summer's scorching heat, Casual Friday
has given way to Casual Every Day. And conventions are crumbling as
old-economy companies find themselves competing for scarce labor
against new-media enterprises run by people who take their fashion
cues from Silicon Valley, not Saville Row. Clifford Grodd,
president and chief executive at Paul Stuart, the Madison Avenue
store, said of the trend, ``These companies are shooting themselves
in the foot by letting down their standards.'' (Fred R. Conrad/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT48) WASHINGTON -- April 5, 2000 -- SCI-BIOTECH-FOOD --
Environmental and consumer groups protested Wednesday outside the
National Academy of Sciences offices in Washington after the
academy gingerly endorsed the safety of biotech foods now on the
market. Despite the endorsement, the Academy called for stronger
regulation of the novel plants. (Paul Hosefros/The New York Times)
</P>
